The paper deals with lower bounds on the redundancy of PIR codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of algebraic structures and linear span also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to security and privacy (cs.SI) since PIR codes are used to protect sensitive data.
